AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - CAPE VERDE
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Fri, 06 Feb 1998 13:33:11 -0500
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol 11-No 6.

Dr. G. Carvalho Silva, Director of Veterinary Services in Praia, Cape Verde
reported an outbreak of African swine fever to the Office International des
Epizooties (OIE) on 5 Feb 1998.
Location No. of outbreaks
Santiago island (rural areas of Trindade, ?
S. Martinho, Ponta do Sol and Ponta Furna,
in Tarrafal)

The report to OIE was not as inclusive of detail as is normally seen.
However, it appears that all susceptible animals have contracted the
disease and that 85-100% have died.
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: laboratory diagnosis and confirmation
by INIA-CISA (OIE Reference Laboratory for African swine fever in Madrid)
on 4 February 1998.
Control measures during reporting period: control and eradication measures
have been taken by Veterinary Authorities.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
